

IAM: Users & Groups

  IAM is a global services. You cannot choose a region for it

  -IAM = indentity and acces management, global service
  -Root account: created by default.
  -Users are pepople within your organization, and can be gruped
  -Groups only contain users, not other Groups
  -User dont have to belong to a group, and users can belong to multiple groups

 IAM PERSMISSIONS

  -Users or groups can be assigned JSON document calle policies
  -these policies define the permissions of the users
  -In AWS you apply the least privilege principle: Dont give more permissions than a user needs
